n class=title> Re: anyone here planning of becoming an anime artist?</span><hr size=1> There is nothing that I could think of that would be greater than being an anime artist. Unfortunitly, anime and comics are shunned in the world of American art. It's very hard to succeed. Also... doesn't it seem like there is some sort of &quot;rule&quot; against American Anime-artists succeeding? There are tons of them out there, and yet, I don't know of one who has made it. With the exception of that guy who does Gold Diggers. (I think. I don't know much about it)<br>Anyway, my advice is to secure a good job first (webdesigner for me :D) and then try to establish yourself in the art world. And always practice realism and still life. Nobody takes you seriously unless you have a few of those in your portfolio...<br>Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwithroo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Withroo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/21/02 12:22:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3421.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/withroo/hisoka5.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: anyone here planning of becoming an anime artist?</span><hr size=1> What StormyLuvsYou says is true.<br><br>Anime-esque art isn't as appreciated as much over here, and in Asia, where manganess all began, it's a shrinking field, I do believe. It's harder to be successful in the manga/anime field now than before.<br><br>You could become an animator, working for a large company, but only if you fancy colouring nothing but pre-drawn line art and so on.<br><br>The manga/anime field isn't very stable, as two important ingredients are needed: good writing skills and visual arts talent. If you're only good at one, it's best you either try a different line of work, since working collaborations between writers and artists are rare (in the manga field, that is).<br><br>So stick to what StormyLuvsYou said. Get yourself a stable job, establish yourself (and your portfolio), and be active. Job offers won't scurry to you; you have to go after the oppertunities yourself. <p><center><hr width=50%><br><br><table width="240" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/withroo/mokona1.gif" alt="Puu!"></td><td><p align=left><font color="FFCCCC" size="-1"><small>I am cute.<br><br>Give me a <a href="http://pub58.ezboard.com/bthewartowerthefortrestofdoom">cookie</a>,<br><br>And feed my <a href="http://www.livejournal.com/~jezebel_complex">ego</a>.</font></td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=3421.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=3421.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3421.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=3421.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=3421.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><